The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 20 May is 42,102 (4,873 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 15 May, there were 81 new confirmed cases (9.4 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 08 May, there were 99 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 18% (18 fewer cases).
